<p>V. Verlaine, <i>Parsifal</i>. [Eliot's note]
        Verlaine's sonnet describes Parsifal, the questing
        knight, resisting all sensual temptations to keep himself
        pure for the Grail; Wagner's Parsifal had his feet washed
        before entering the castle of the Grail.</p>
